// Goal: (r1@ == self_@ && r2@ == self_@) ==> r1.id == r2.id
    //
    // The premises only give r1.id@ == self_.id@ and r2.id@ == self_.id@
    // (Seq<u8> equality, via the open spec view of EndPoint), which
    // chain transitively to r1.id@ == r2.id@. However, Verus models
    // Vec<u8> as an external_body type with no axiom relating view
    // equality to Vec spec-equality, so r1.id@ == r2.id@ does NOT
    // imply r1.id == r2.id. clone_up_to_view itself is external_body
    // with only an `ensures res@ == self@` clause, so no additional
    // structural information is available about r1.id and r2.id.
    // Hence the postcondition is not derivable under the current
    // axiom set.
    assert((r1@ == self_@ && r2@ == self_@) ==> r1.id@ == r2.id@);
